Round the dock blur mask a bit more in Tahoe Dark so it does not poke out.

The blur region is a rounded rectangle whose corner radius equals blurRadius.
It overflows the (more rounded) background pill wherever the mask corners are
squarer than the pill -- smaller blurRadius => squarer => more overflow. At the
default 24 a small frosted nub still stuck out of the corner, so bump it to 32
(rounder mask, still within the pill's rectangle, never larger than it).

Increasing the radius only rounds the corners more; the ellipses stay inside the
[0,0,w,h] rect, so this cannot enlarge the blur region.

The trailing tab after the file name in the --- / +++ lines is required so that
patch(1) does not truncate the "Tahoe Dark" path at the space.
--- a/package/contents/skins/Tahoe Dark/Config.qml	
+++ b/package/contents/skins/Tahoe Dark/Config.qml	
@@ -8,7 +8,7 @@ QtObject {
     property string imageRight: "bgr.png"
     property string imagetask: "tasks.svgz"
     property bool blur: true
-    property int blurRadius: 24
+    property int blurRadius: 32
     property int positionTaskIndicator: 9
     property int leftMargin: 20
     property int topMargin: 20
